GLM.expon

Fabian Blombach

07/06/2019

This script describes the generation of generalised linear models for the progression of TEC-Spt4/5-Elf1 into productive transcription during exponential growth. Negative binomial models were used to model count data that showed overdispersion. Raw coverage of Elf1 in the TU body region was modelled. The normalisation against the chromatin input was built into the model by including an offest term with raw chromatin input coverage.

export PATH=$PATH:/Users/fabianblombach/miniconda3/bin
mkdir temp
bedtools slop -i $TSS -g  ../Genomes/Sso_NCBI/SsoP2.sizes -s -l 7 -r 4 > temp/slop.bed

bedtools getfasta -name -s -bed temp/slop.bed -fi ../Genomes/Sso_NCBI/NC_002754.fna -fo temp/DNA.fasta
## mkdir: temp: File exists
#Temperature in Kelvin (Sulfolobus growth temperature of 76 degr Celsius)
temp=349.15
#Salt concentration in molar
salt= 0.025

#load reference values from SantaLucia Jr paper (PNAS 1998)
NN<-read.table("~/HTS/scripts/NN_thermodynamics.txt", header=T, sep="\t")
NN$H<-as.numeric(as.character(NN$H))
NN$S<-as.numeric(as.character(NN$S))
#delH is in kcal/mol, while delS is in cal/mol*k, calculate the delG in kcal/mol
NN$G <- NN$H - (NN$S*temp/1000)

#load alignment of promoter sequences (output from bedtools getfasta -tab)
require(seqinr)
input<-read.fasta("temp/DNA.fasta", forceDNAtolower=T)
mono<-as.data.frame(matrix(unlist(input), nrow=length(input), byrow=T), row.names=names(input))
row.names(mono)<-gsub('(+)',"",row.names(mono), fixed=T)
row.names(mono)<-gsub('(-)',"",row.names(mono), fixed=T)
# loop to make table with dinucleotides
dinuc<-matrix(rep("N", times=nrow(mono)*(ncol(mono)-1)), nrow=nrow(mono))
for (j in 1:nrow(mono)) {
  for (i in 1:(ncol(mono)-1)) { 
  dinuc[j,i] <- paste0(mono[j,i], mono[j,i+1]) 
  } 
}
# replace dinucleotides with corresponding deltaG values
dinucG<-dinuc
for (k in 1:16) {
dinucG[dinucG == NN[k,1]]<- NN[k,4]
}
dinucG<-data.frame(matrix(as.numeric(dinucG), ncol=ncol(dinuc)))

calculate Elf1Bd and input occupancy for linear modelling

export PATH=$PATH:/Users/fabianblombach/miniconda3/bin

#calculate input coverage
computeMatrix reference-point --sortRegions keep -bs 1 -a 500 -b 0 -R $TSS -S $Inp1 $Inp2 $Spt45_r1 $Spt45_r2 $Elf1_r1 $Elf1_r2 -o temp/trashme.npz --outFileNameMatrix temp/trashme.tab;
rm temp/trashme.npz;
head -n 2 temp/trashme.tab > temp/Coverage.tab; 
tail -n $nrows temp/trashme.tab >> temp/Coverage.tab; rm temp/trashme.tab

read matrix file and split based on samples

cov <- read.table(paste0("temp/Coverage.tab"), sep="\t", header=F)
Inp1_bodyCov <- rowMeans(cov[,251:500])
Inp2_bodyCov <- rowMeans(cov[,751:1000])
Spt45_r1_bodyCov <- rowMeans(cov[,1251:1500])
Spt45_r2_bodyCov <- rowMeans(cov[,1751:2000])
Elf1_r1_bodyCov <- rowMeans(cov[,2251:2500])
Elf1_r2_bodyCov <- rowMeans(cov[,2751:3000])

covMeans<-data.frame(Inp1_bodyCov, Inp2_bodyCov, Spt45_r1_bodyCov, Spt45_r2_bodyCov, Elf1_r1_bodyCov, Elf1_r2_bodyCov)

Calculate G for -7 ot +5 width = 12 by summing up dinucleotide G values

width = 12
  deltaG <- rowSums(dinucG[,1:11]) - 0.114*(width-1)*log(salt) 
dataMerged<-data.frame(deltaG, covMeans)
row.names(dataMerged)<-row.names(mono)
dataMerged<- merge(dataMerged, data, by.x="row.names", by.y="operon_id", sort=F)

#filter out TUs with bad RNAP recruitment (SSO8620 and SSO2036)

Automatic model selection with step() function including binary interaction terms

#function to calculate BIC
bic<-function(model) {-model$twologlik  + (length(model$coefficients)+1) * log(nrow(model$model))}

model.null<- suppressWarnings(glm.nb(Elf1_r1_bodyCov ~ offset(log(Inp1_bodyCov)), data=dataMerged2, maxit=100))
#full model including all binary interaction terms
model.bin <- suppressWarnings(glm.nb(Elf1_r1_bodyCov ~ offset(log(Inp1_bodyCov)) + log(elf1_r1_promoter) + deltaG + log(TFB1_foldR1) + log(TFEb_foldR1) + log(cpsf1_r1_promoter) + I(log(elf1_r1_promoter)*deltaG) + I(log(elf1_r1_promoter)*log(TFB1_foldR1)) + I(log(elf1_r1_promoter)*log(TFEb_foldR1)) + I(log(elf1_r1_promoter)*log(cpsf1_r1_promoter)) + I(deltaG*log(TFB1_foldR1)) + I(deltaG*log(TFEb_foldR1)) + I(deltaG*log(cpsf1_r1_promoter)) + I(log(TFB1_foldR1)*log(TFEb_foldR1)) + I(log(TFB1_foldR1)*log(cpsf1_r1_promoter)) + I(log(TFEb_foldR1)*log(cpsf1_r1_promoter)), data=dataMerged2, maxit=100))

model.step<-suppressWarnings(step(object=model.null, scope=list(upper=model.bin$call, lower=model.null$call), data=dataMerged2, trace=F, maxit=100, direction = "forward", k = log(nrow(dataMerged2))))
bic(model.step)
## [1] 1812.507
#trying to add single terms to starting model
model.step.spt45<-suppressWarnings(step(object=update(model.null,  ~ . + log(elf1_r1_promoter)), scope=list(upper=model.bin$call, lower=~1), data=dataMerged2, trace=F, maxit=100, direction = "forward", k = log(nrow(dataMerged2))))
bic(model.step.spt45)
## [1] 1812.507
model.step.deltaG<-suppressWarnings(step(object=update(model.null,  ~ . + deltaG), scope=list(upper=model.bin$call, lower=~1), data=dataMerged2, trace=F, direction = "forward", k = log(nrow(dataMerged2))))
bic(model.step.deltaG)
## [1] 1816.723
model.step.TFB<-suppressWarnings(step(object=update(model.null,  ~ . + log(TFB1_foldR1)), scope=list(upper=model.bin$call, lower=~1), data=dataMerged2, trace=F, maxit=100, direction = "forward", k = log(nrow(dataMerged2))))
bic(model.step.TFB)
## [1] 1817.301
model.step.TFEb<-suppressWarnings(step(object=update(model.null,  ~ . + log(TFEb_foldR1)), scope=list(upper=model.bin$call, lower=~1), data=dataMerged2, trace=F, maxit=100, direction = "forward", k = log(nrow(dataMerged2))))
bic(model.step.TFEb)
## [1] 1817.379
model.step.cpsf1<-suppressWarnings(step(object=update(model.null,  ~ . + log(cpsf1_r1_promoter)), scope=list(upper=model.bin$call, lower=~1), data=dataMerged2, trace=F, maxit=100, direction = "forward", k = log(nrow(dataMerged2))))
bic(model.step.cpsf1)
## [1] 1812.507
#optimized model
